Salmon Teriyaki
http://www.thepeachkitchen.com/2015/09/salmon-teriyaki/

3/4 cup soy sauce
6 tbsp sugar
3 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tbsp ginger
1 tbsp cornstarch dissolved in 1 tbsp water

2 salmon fillets
2 bowls of cooked rice
3 cups fresh spinach
3 cloves garlic, minced
salt and pepper
sesame seeds and spring onions for garnish

Preheat oven to 400 F

Combine soy sauce, sugar and ginger in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil with constant stirring.
Add rice vinegar. Simmer for a few seconds.
Adjust sweetness to your liking by adding sugar.
If you want to thicken the sauce, add 1 tbsp cornstarch mixture then wait
for it to boil again.

Lightly oil a baking pan,
Place salmon fillets on the pan and brush with teriyaki sauce. Make sure
you coat it well.
Bake until the fish flakes easily with a fork, about 14-15 minutes.
In a non-stick skillet, saute garlic and 1 tbsp canola oil. Add fresh
spinach. Keep sauteeing until spinach is wilted.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve salmon immediately with rice and sauteed spinach.
